                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.512/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sevier</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 15, 1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Your telegram No. 92, September 26, 1934. You are authorized to settle the
                    accounts referred to therein, including the payment of tax. With regard to your
                    despatch No. 137, July 3, 1934, you are referred to the Department’s instruction
                    No. 8, January 10, 1934, and instructed to renew your protest against the
                    Chilean sales tax in accord with the views set forth in that instruction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
